  <content-type name="widget_teaserGrid">
    <ui:label>Teaser Grid widget</ui:label>
    <ui:icon>widget</ui:icon>
    <ui:description>A widget to pick related views.</ui:description>
    <doc:description xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      <p>
        This widget allows content editors to put desked teasers into
        multiple columns. There is a special group
        named
        <em>grid</em>
        in content section page. This is where
        content editors can put the desked teasers into nested groups to
        show them in multiple columns in the page. It is possible to select
        a specific grid group of a specific section to render
        the teasers. The name of the group is configurable from
        <em>TeaserGridDefaultProcessor.properties</em>
        . Currently available
        nested groups are:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <em>Two column</em>
          group
        </li>
        <li>
          <em>Three column</em>
          group
        </li>
        <li>
          <em>Row</em>
          and
          <em>Column</em>
          group
        </li>
        <li>
          <em>Two column(1+N)</em>
          group: shows 1 item in the first column and fills
          the second column with rest of the items in the group
        </li>
        <li>
          <em>Two column(N+1)</em>
          group: Shows all the items inside this group in the
          first column except the final item is shown in the second column.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The desked teasers are rendered by related Teaser Views. In order for this
        method to work you have to drop suitably configured Teaser View widgets onto this
        widget's
        <em class="guilabel">Related view</em>
        field (in the
        <em class="guilabel">Related content</em>
        pane at the bottom of the default tab). All the Teaser Views in the
        <em class="guilabel">Related view</em>
        field are used to render the results. The intention is that these Teaser Views are configured
        with selection criteria so that different types of results are rendered in different ways based on their
        content type. Currently teaser grid widget don't support rendering different types of results
        based on their position (as it is done in the view picker widget). For further
        information, see
        the description of the
        <em class="guilabel">Related view</em>
        field.
      </p>
    </doc:description>
    <ui:title-field>title</ui:title-field>
    <parameter name="com.escenic.article.staging" value="false" />
    <panel name="general">
      <ui:label>General</ui:label>
      <ui:description>The basic configuration fields</ui:description>
      <ref-field-group name="basic-widget-fields" />
      <ref-field-group name="teaserGrid-widget-selection-fields" />
      <!--<ref-field-group name="embedded-datasource-field-group"/>-->
      <!--<ui:ref-relation-type ref="datasourceRelation"/>-->
    </panel>
